<section class="section-shell section-shell--contrast">
  <div class="container trust-grid">
    <article class="trust-card">
      <h3>Common urgent triggers</h3>
      <p>
        Burning odor, melted devices, repeated tripping, buzzing panels, storm
        damage, flooded electrical areas, or unexplained loss of power to
        critical circuits.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="trust-card">
      <h3>What to do first</h3>
      <p>
        If it is safe, stop using the affected circuit or equipment. Document
        what happened, when it started, and what loads were running at the time.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="trust-card">
      <h3>What happens next</h3>
      <p>
        The goal is to stabilize the situation, identify the likely cause, and
        determine whether the issue is isolated, systemic, or part of a larger
        upgrade need.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
